msgid "Installing on OSX"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing_blender/osx.rst:6
msgid ""
"Check the :doc:`minimum requirements and where to get Blender "
"</getting_started/installing_blender/installing>`, if you haven't done so "
"yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing_blender/osx.rst:9
msgid ""
"After downloading Blender for Mac-OSX, uncompress the file and drag "
"``blender.app`` onto the Applications folder. Alternatively, you can launch "
"Blender directly from the uncompressed folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing_blender/osx.rst:14
msgid ""
"Because *Blender* doesn't use the standard OS menu system, you likely have a"
" redundant menu-bar at the top."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/getting_started/installing_blender/osx.rst:17
msgid ""
"To remove it see `this post "
"<http://www.macworld.com/article/55321/2007/02/hidemenubar.html>`__ on "
"Macworld, but beware that it is somewhat complex. As an alternative: simply "
"make *Blender* full screen with the last button in the info window header "
"(most times at the top of the screen layout)."
msgstr ""
